{
  "texts": [
    "LLaMA-ENC and PMC-LLaMA-ENC: While LLaMA and PMC-LLaMA are known for their performance in text generation tasks, we also experiment with them as encoder models by passing a full attention mask and sampling the embedding from the last token.",
    "This allows for a direct comparison to be made with the aforementioned BERT-like models, which are also encoder-based.",
    "Implementation details.",
    "Our models are all trained using the AdamW optimizer 28 with a learning rate of 2e-5.",
    "The max context length is set as 512, and the batch size is 128."
  ]
}